data.title: Mrs. Anna Lee Moore
data.text:
YPSILANTI - Mrs. Anna Lee Moore, 70 years old, wife of Samuel J. Moore, Detroit, died last night in a local hospital after an illness of 16 months.

She was born June 23, 1873, in Dexter, a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Levi R. Lee, and was married there on Sept. 13, 1895, to Mr. Moore. The couple lived in Detroit many years.

Surviving are the husband and two sons, Lt. Robert L. Moore, in the Navy; and Lt. Richard R. Moore, in the Army, stationed now at Denver.

Funeral services will be held at 1 o'clock Thursday afternoon at the Moore funeral home here, with Rev. Raymon B. Bair officiating. Burial will be in Acacia Park cemetery, at 13-mile Rd. and Southfield Highway.

Friends may call at the funeral home.
